Color-changeable chewing gum (Masticatory Performance Evaluating Gum Xylitol, Lotte, Japan) was evaluated, as described by Hama et al. [33]. The participants were instructed to chew the gum 60 times freely, at a speed of one chewing cycle per second. The chewed gum was flattened to a thickness of 1.5 mm by compression in polyethylene films between two glass plates and evaluated immediately after chewing. Then, L*, a*, and b* values were measured using a colorimeter (CR-13, Konica-Minolta Sensing, Japan) using the CIECLB color system at five points: the center and approximately 3 mm above, below, to the right, and to the left of the center. ΔE values were evaluated using the following formula:
